name: Mission's "La Lengua"
description:
Sunny apt in a great corner of the Mission. You will be busy just doing everything nearby and then there is all of SF to explore

The space
room in a 2 bedroom near it all in the Mission District, including BART. Internet, parking if you want, $10/night. Within blocks of 20 great places, including the #1 burrito in the US of A at La Tacqueria. Within a mile of there are probably another 50, the Mission is pretty great for food, shopping, music and parks. I am a mellow host, pretty busy working professional, who can point you to lots of great walks, runs and bike rides around SF and Bay Area. You don't need a car to do a lot here. House is very bike/pedestrian friendly, I can show you lots of good walks and rides.

Guest access
house, books, internet
No TV - you won't miss it.

Other things to note
Mission near me, and you could spend days just staying close to house, but all of SF is amazing, and easy to ge
neighborhood_overview: great food, bars, and walk to everything, included local theater (ATA), cinema (Roxie), and its easy enough to walk to a few other great places (Bernal Heights, Noe Valley)
host_about: I am an accountant and do lots of stuff that is not very accountant like.  I think SF is amazing, and traveling in general, hope guests come and have a great time exploring far and wide.  I don't have a car, and you certainly do not need one when you are here!  Come enjoy the hills, the views (the former arent that hard to climb and the latter are worth it) .  And bring a sweater, cause we dont understand summer the way other places do

name: Loft-like Apt./Garden
description:
Located on 26th St. in wonderful Noe Valley, this beautifully large furnished open apartment (540 square feet) with separate street level entrance in a two unit building. We live in the upstairs unit. Four windows open onto the quiet rear of the house and a private entrance to a private beautifully landscaped garden.

The space
Located on 26th St. in wonderful Noe Valley, this beautifully large furnished open apartment (540 square feet) with separate street level entrance in a two unit building. We live in the upstairs unit. Four windows open onto the quiet rear of the house and a private entrance to a private beautifully landscaped garden.

The apt. has everything needed in a fully equipped modern kitchen - stainless steel appliances (GE refrigerator, & gas stove with oven, stainless steel sink & garbage disposal and Bosch dishwasher), caesarstone counter and maple cabinets.

The beautifully done bath includes a glass enclosed full size bath
neighborhood_overview: We love Noe Valley. It is a wonderful friendly upscale neighborhood. There is a terrific mix of people who live here, many commute to Silicon Valley via (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) busses that stop a few blocks away from our home. There are lots of charming stores and restaurants within walking distance and our location makes it easily accessible to all parts of San Francisco by public transportation. Noe Valley also has more dogs (pets) than any other part of San Francisco.
host_about: Arlene is originally from New York and grew up in the Bronx, and Leon is a third generation San Franciscan. We are both retired. Leon loves to ski and play tennis.  Arlene is involved in local community services (Neighborhood Community Court and San Francisco's Civil Grand Jury).We love to travel and have visited many interesting cultures and countries (i.e. China, India, Vietnam). We enjoy trying new restaurants and taking part in the culture that SF has to offer. We are outgoing and friendly, but respect our guests privacy. We love meeting new people from all over the world, and that is what makes our hosting so much fun.

name: Nice Rooms With Private 1/2 Bath
description:
The space
Please come and enjoy our master bedroom suite with a private 1/2 bath, in an 1880's Victorian in sunny Noe Valley. Centrally located to Noe's shops and easy walking distance to Valencia corridor, Dolores Park and the Mission, along with public transportation a block away.

The guest suite is two rooms with a bay window in the bedroom (queen size bed) and a decorative fireplace in the sitting room; these are joined in the middle by a vanity with a sink and an enclosed toilet across from a large closet. The main bath is located off the kitchen and is equipped with an Ofuro tub and shower.

The neighborhood has a small town feel, while being a half hour to downtown (on public transportation) or an hour to Napa or Silicon Valleys (by car; traffic permitting). Yet, it is only a short walk to all the smaller dynamic locations for dining, arts and cultural events.

neighborhood_overview:
Pacific Heights is one of the nicest historic neighborhoods that is centrally located in San Francisco.
Walking distance to five grocery stores - three blocks to either Whole Foods (one the corner or California street and Franklin street) or Molly Stones (on California street, after you pass Fillmore street). To mor4 blocks to Trader JoeÃ¢â¬â¢s and two SafewayÃ¢â¬â¢s - I e south and one north from my home, 5 minutes drive. Also fun grocery Japanese supermarket - 3 blocks and another ethnic one - Woori, Korean market.

ItÃ¢â¬â¢s a great place to hike and run. I usually run to the Bay and sometimes to the Golden Gate Bridge and back through Lyon Stairs. Very scenic route. There are lost of beautiful parks close to my home. The closest park is just a 1.5 blocks away - on Laguna and Sacramento street.

My home is located close to the famous Fillmore Street and an easy walk to Union Street. Both streets are a shopping heaven. Also there are many great restaurants walking distan
host_about:
I am a physician and I moved to USA 22 years ago. I love what San Francisco city and the Bay Area has to offer. I feel very lucky and privileged to live in a beautiful and safe area of San Francisco called Pacific Heights. 

I am an avid mountaineer/climber and I travel usually once a year, for a month - long expedition trip. That is usually when I open the calendar in AirBnB for my apartment, as well as (separately) for my garage. 

I would like to rent my beautiful home to someone reliable for all that time when I am gone. 

The things I can't live without are my family, friends, mountains, my amazing home, nature, meditation and any kind of physical activity daily. 

My favorite travel destinations - to many to mention. I feel amazing in high altitude mountains. 

I climbed all the highest mountains in the world called Seven Summits (including Mt.Everest), as well as skied to the South Pole.  Beside that, all my travels and expeditions left me with amazing memories. 

My favorite books - too many to list here as I  read a lot, but I love the most  "Master and Margarita" by Michail Bulhakov. There are many books in my home, so if you have time feel free to read something new. I switched now to ebooks or audiobooks, as it doesn't take any physical space. 

My favorite food is prepared with local and organic ingredients - check out many restaurants on Fillmore street - you will have so many to choose from, even after Pandemic years. I love sushi and the best sushi in the city is a walking distance from my home - check out Tataki restaurant (on California street/Divisadero street) - amazing and fresh! 
I also would encourage you to check Ã¢â¬ÅState Bird ProvisionsÃ¢â¬Â, but you would need a reservation. ItÃ¢â¬â¢s a 7 -10 minutes walking distance from my home. Located on Fillmore street. 

I travel a lot for business - Marriott hotels, but for fun - I prefer staying in a tent or in a cool Airbnb place in different cities all over the world. 

My motto in life is to live largely, Ã¢â¬Åon the edge of my comfort zone", hence climbing or polar expeditions, and now posting my home at Airbnb website. 

Throughout the process of renting my home I learn that my HOAÃ¢â¬â¢s CC&Rs (Homeowners Rules) do not allow for any short term rentals and I can only rent it for a month or longer. 

My modern apartment is located on the top floor of the beautiful Victorian (freshly painted) building (originally from 1896). I have the best view of Japan Town and Twin Towers as well as complete privacy in my home. 

I love green plants and I have many in my home and at the balcony. IÃ¢â¬â¢ll be very grateful if you could please water it once a week ( just a little bit :) to keep it lush and green. 

So far, I had wonderful guests from all over the world for the last ten years. I am super grateful for all people I met through AirBnB. 

Please feel free to ask me any questions before you send a reservation. 

I look forward to meeting you in person and to host you in my home.
 
Thank you.

name: Cottage in the Mission
description:
A large pleasant private bedroom in the carriage house at the rear of a SF Victorian on a quiet tree lined street. Hardwood floors, windows look out on sunny courtyard, which is yours to enjoy as well!
Listing ID: STR-010853

The space
Come stay in our secluded cottage in the heart of the Mission district, the sunniest neighborhood in San Francisco. There are many micro-climates of SF and the mission's geographical location insulates it from the fog and cold air of the west, keeping in warm and sunny most of the year.

Spend your time tucked away in our courtyard/ garden oasis, where you'll relax in the sun along side jasmine, french lavender, trumpet flowers, and wisteria with friendly kitties to keep you company.

Built in 1905, this cozy cottage situated on a quiet tree lined block, has everything you'll need for an unforgettable stay in San Francisco! All with in one block you can find nice new local restaurants, coffee houses, a bar
host_about:
I am an artist specializing in painting, printmaking and photography. I was born and raised in San Francisco and love living and working here! I like going to the cinema, especially to see foreign and independent films. And I love to hike along the ocean with my camera in hand, discovering new trails around the California coast.

I like to travel. I have been to Amsterdam, Paris and Berlin, all of which I loved! I've traveled to Yelapa, Mexico, in the heart of the jungle and I really enjoyed that also. There is really no kind of travel I don't like.

host_about:
My Motto; "Every Day is a Good Day!"

*As of February 27, 2022  I was fully vaccinated by way of the Pfizer all available vaccine and the two boosters available. I also contracted Covid 19 or a variant in May 2022 and fully recovered.

Something about me and my home; IÃ¢â¬â¢m gay, 64, single, very fit and energetic, very outgoing and easy going. I have always lived in California and have traveled the world extensively. I absolutely love San Francisco and even more being in the Mission District. Entrepreneurial spirited, at age twenty-one I started a business which fulfilled insurersÃ¢â¬â¢ responsibilities for auto losses involving vandalism and retired from that adventure just shy of 36 years later.  I have been vegan for four years now and I have redirected my culinary skills towards all things plant, sugar-free, and fat-free based cuisine.  I enjoy practicing yoga at Love Story just around the corner.  I am also an avid bicyclist and use my bike as my primary mode of transport in the city.  I am attending  Community College SF working my way to a zoological degree. Life is good.

As for my home, the location and views are arguably the best the Mission District can offer. The private roof deck, a green oasis for the otherwise concrete jungle of a Mission Street residence. My place faces west so it's on the street side and is usually quite noisy from people, traffic and sirens. Thankfully the residence was constructed in 2008 and  built  quite soundproof. The bedrooms are well sized and comfortably appointed. The sun always seems to shine in the Mission District.

Finally, I love being an AirBnB host which allows me to share my good fortune, meet wonderful people and make new friends. 

I hope that you choose to stay. 

Mark

An alcove contains a 4 cu ft refrigerator, microwave oven, coffee maker, toaster and a small supply of eating utensils. A small dining table will allow casual eating and refreshments. neighborhood_overview: We are located just minutes from the heart of the Mission and famous Valencia St. with its thousands of restaurant seats and fabulous shopping. Within a four block radius, you will find four restaurants that appear in the Chronical's 100 best as well as a bar cited for its food and cocktails. There are four newly opened art galleries. Within a 10 minute stroll, you can eat casually at numerous Mexican, Vietnamese, Peruvian, Korean, Japanese,and Chinese restaurants at reasonable prices. Friendly coffee shops with Wi-Fi abound. Chains like Starbucks and Peets as well as Mission originals, Gourmet food trucks serve goodies from streets and designated parking areas.
host_about:
Your co-hosts are Ingrid and Betty. Ingrid is a top hair stylist at one of San FranciscoÃ¢â¬â¢s elite salons near Union Square. She is outgoing, enthusiastic and enjoys meeting and working with people. An avid and knowledgably sports fan, Ingrid and her partner, Jacquay, occupy the remainder of the flat and though they are full time workers can be called on to assist guests when home.

Betty, an artist and poet, is IngridÃ¢â¬â¢s mother and occupies the upper flat with her husband, Joe, a retired architecture professor .  After teaching careers in Ann Arbor, Michigan, they have lived in SF since 1988 except for four years in Hong Kong when Joe was called on to help start a new Dept of Architecture at the Chinese University of Hong Kong. This project provided opportunities for new international friendships and foreign travel. During these Hong Kong years Betty completed and showed a series of large Paintings, based on images and stories from the South China Morning Post. Betty and Joe have been active in the arts throughout their lives. They were involved in performance arts groups in the 60Ã¢â¬â¢s and 70Ã¢â¬â¢s and helped establish the Ann Arbor Experimental Film Festival. 

Being retired, Betty and Joe are available most of the time to answer questions or solve problems. They have travelled extensively during their life and despite living at one time or another in Boston, New York, Ann Arbor, Newfoundland and Hong Kong, are tickled to now call San Francisco home. They know and love the city and will be happy to make recommendations or help in any way possible. However, if you are not looking for social contact, you can stay with here with complete privacy.

name: Explore Golden Gate Park from a Sunny Garden Guest Suite
description:
Live like a local in a welcoming, convenient, private 4 room guest suite in San Francisco's Richmond District. Shop for groceries nearby and cook simple meals. Relax on a couch in a sunny window. Explore a backyard with a deck, lawn, fire pit and BBQ.

An entire lower level in our 90 year old arts and crafts style home in the heart of one of SF's most diverse and authentic neighborhoods.

Large, private bedroom with queen bed and full sized closet sleeps 2. Air mattress can be deployed in the living room to sleep an additional 2 adults if needed.

Comfortable living room with TV, bright orange couch and expandable dining table seats 4. Amazon Fire stick, Wi-Fi, and a Nintendo Wii provide some entertainment options as well.

Kitchenette includes large fridge, electric cooking range, microwave and toaster oven and other misc items for light duty meals.

Backyard with deck and BBQ is open to guests too.

Secure, private entrance
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is in the Richmond District, a hidden gem of a neighborhood. There's easy access to Golden Gate Park, the largest green space in San Francisco. Many food and drink options are nearby, as well as coffee shops and grocery stores. The apartment is located along a main bus line with service direct to Downtown and Ocean Beach.
host_about:
We (Adam and Roz) are a married couple with a love for world travel, live music, new food and drink experiences, and a small white fluffy dogs named Rupert.

We love sharing our home and introducing visitors to some of the lesser known parts of the city we live in.

We both keep busy with full-time day jobs and two children but are always happy to help make your stay as pleasant and memorable as possible.

name: Beautiful, modern and super located
description:
Cow Hollow is a beautifully classic San Francisco neighborhood with an interesting mix of architectural styles. Two blocks from the Bay, equi-walking distance from urban and natural attractions. Boutique shopping, bars and restaurants are a couple blocks away on both Union and Chestnut streets. Walk to grocery stores, bookshops, ice cream parlors, the library and movie theaters.

The space
The space is incredible really. Living room has 50" screen TV above a gas fireplace to warm you up after cruising around this great city. High ceilings, and new modern furniture. The dining room has a gorgeous glass table that seats six comfortably. The kitchen is modern and stylish, remodeled in April 2013 with a wine fridge, eat in counter and a small deck with a table and two chairs. There is a washer and dryer in the unit in a fun secret hiding place...

You can expect to have the perfect stay one block from Union Street, three blocks from Chestnut street where you
host_about:
Hi I'm a professional woman who loves to dance, cook, do yoga and windsurf.  I come from New Jersey, have lived in Paris but have spent most of my adult life living in the SF Bay Area. Come stay in my wonderful space in the best situated neighborhood, in the prettiest US city and one of the best in the world if you like to walk, eat and be outside. 

The reviews speak for themselves as we are dedicated to you having the perfect stay for your new job, internship or just exploring your next city to live.

description:
Spacious, well-cleaned San Francisco home in wonderful Glen Park. Five minute walk to BART then ten minutes to Downtown. Hi-speed WiFi and free two-car parking! Three bedrooms and three bathrooms, especially, a big plus. Two queen sofa beds. Extra family room with TV. Short walk to cafes, a variety of restaurants and a great food market. Across the street from a wonderful park with hiking trails and a playground. Near bus lines to Golden Gate Park. Families, groups and business ready.

The space
We want to let all our guests know that all surfaces in our house, T.V. remotes, light switches, doorhandles will be completely cleaned with lysol spray and all towels and sheets washed in hot water. We also leave two nights and three days between reservations for your safety.
Our comfortable, spacious home is in the wonderful Glen Park neighborhood: three bedrooms and three bathrooms and family room plus two sofa beds. We are tolerant people and enjoy welcomi

We are across the street from Glen Park canyon with great hiking trails and a playground and five blocks from Glen Park-- a wonderful and thriving neighborhood--with the BART to take you downtown in ten minutes and great restaurants, cafes, a new library, a bookstore and a market. These are some of the places in our neighborhood!

host_about:
We love keeping active, body, mind and soul.  Jim retired as director of a senior citizens center, and Louise retired as an English and creative writing professor at the local community college. She now teaches small memoir workshops and Jim taught history classes for while and is now doing a history of his family as well as house projects and walks.
 Louise writes and is working on her fifth book. We both love to interact with people of all ages and we are tolerant and open people. Jim  loves to read and keep up with the news and seeing art. We both love reading both fiction and non-fiction,  visiting museums, watching movies, seeing plays, visiting with family and friends and experiencing the great outdoors. We love meeting new people from all around the world. We travel back East once a year to visit family, and Louise recently taught a workshop in St. Thomas where her sister lives. We love to travel in California, as well. Louise went to the U. of Wisconsin and keeps up with college friends and she and Jim both attended the University of Buffalo. neighborhood_overview: It's The Mission District. a bit gritty but the place to be stationed. Named for Mission Dolores founded in 1776, San FranciscoÃ¢â¬â¢s oldest neighborhood has some of its hottest new restaurants and galleries. Bernal Heights, Potrero Hill These neighborhoods all share a sunny outlook. Boasting some of the best weather in the city, the Mission District, Bernal Heights and Potrero Hill take advantage of an abundance of fog-free days. New restaurants and night spots are a draw while Mission Dolores, 16th and Dolores streets, is the oldest structure in San Francisco. Many of the cityÃ¢â¬â¢s pioneers are buried in an adjacent cemetery. The largest concentration of murals in the city adorn buildings, fences and walls throughout the district. Potrero HillÃ¢â¬â¢s Dogpatch neighborhood is one of 11 historic districts in the city and home to the second crookedest street (after Lombard) in the city.
host_about:
My Motto; "Every Day is a Good Day!"

*As of February 27, 2022  I was fully vaccinated by way of the Pfizer all available vaccine and the two boosters available. I also contracted Covid 19 or a variant in May 2022 and fully recovered.

Something about me and my home; IÃ¢â¬â¢m gay, 64, single, very fit and energetic, very outgoing and easy going. I have always lived in California and have traveled the world extensively. I absolutely love San Francisco and even more being in the Mission District. Entrepreneurial spirited, at age twenty-one I started a business which fulfilled insurersÃ¢â¬â¢ responsibilities for auto losses involving vandalism and retired from that adventure just shy of 36 years later.  I have been vegan for four years now and I have redirected my culinary skills towards all things plant, sugar-free, and fat-free based cuisine.  I enjoy practicing yoga at Love Story just around the corner.  I am also an avid bicyclist and use my bike as my primary mode of transport in the city.  I am attending  Community College SF working my way to a zoological degree. Life is good.

As for my home, the location and views are arguably the best the Mission District can offer. The private roof deck, a green oasis for the otherwise concrete jungle of a Mission Street residence. My place faces west so it's on the street side and is usually quite noisy from people, traffic and sirens. Thankfully the residence was constructed in 2008 and  built  quite soundproof. The bedrooms are well sized and comfortably appointed. The sun always seems to shine in the Mission District.

Finally, I love being an AirBnB host which allows me to share my good fortune, meet wonderful people and make new friends. 

I hope that you choose to stay. 

Mark

name: San Francisco Mid Century Modern with Views
description:
We love welcoming friends from all over the world to our guest house- a two bedroom flat with gorgeous cherry wood floors and a collection of mid century furnishings that we have acquired in our travels. We live on a park and have a nice back yard that you are welcome to use. Our flat is furnished with high quality organic cotton linens and small details that will make you feel at home. Our eclectic neighborhood has the best weather in San Francisco and a community minded vibe!

The space
Our beautiful guest flat is on the first floor of our home and has two bedrooms, a living room, kitchen and bathroom. You have your own entrance. There is a backyard that is accessible through the living room of the flat and is available for your use at any time. Our home sits on a park with tennis courts, basketball courts, a soccer field, baseball diamond, a cement slide, and amazing views of the bay.
We love mid century design and have outfitted our guest flat with furni
neighborhood_overview: Located in the Bayview district, the apartment sits on a park with views of the bay and some of the best weather in San Francisco. The unique area is known for its growing art and food scene, diverse population, and a low key vibe that locals love.
host_about: We love living in San Francisco and enjoying the bountiful diversity our city offers. I'm a restauranteur and chef and feel fortunate to be a part of the Bayview, the community where we live and where both of my restaurants are located. We love seeing and sharing other people's homes in our travels and are excited to welcome people to ours.

name: Gorgeous & stylish unit w/parking
description:
This awesome unit features the latest technology, will provide the most comfortable stay for your trip to SF. Unit comes with a parking spot. Very easy access to underground subway (aka MUNI) about 5 minutes walking distance.

The space
Located in the exclusive residential neighborhood of Forest Hill Extension, a space in our home is now available to you. This unit is located in the downstairs of our home with a separate entrance. This fully-loaded space is enjoyable and relaxing while only being a short ride away from the city life.

To set the right expectations, we built the space to emulate a luxurious hotel room, and it is about the size of a mid-size hotel room. It is the perfect size for a couple, 3 adults or family with 2 small children, but might be a little bit of a tight squeeze for 4 adults.

Guest access
Separate entrance and there is no shared common space. You will have full privacy and access to the amenities provide
neighborhood_overview: The house is in a suburban neighborhood in San Francisco Proper. Although it is not walking distance to the top tourist attractions, it is a very quiet and safe neighborhood, perfect for relaxing a long day of walking. It is about a 5 minute walk from the popular West Portal area, well known for it's excellent neighborhood restaurants, bars and boutiques.
host_about: Bay Area local with plenty of hot tips to make your trip to San Francisco unforgettable.

name: Lovely 3BR Mission Home with Garden
description:
3BR family home, equipped kitchen, dining and living room, side deck and garden. Main floor w/ 3BR for guests. Master suite-occupied by me- on lower level . My suite has separate bath & entrance so guests have privacy. Safety is of prime importance, so I will be social distancing during guest visits, and will not share any spaces with the guests. I have also arranged for extra time between visits so that the entire AirBnB can have a deep disinfecting cleanse. SF STR PERMIT NO. STR 0004 818

The space
Spacious house (1300 sq ft) with beautiful backyard and side deck in the heart of the Mission. The main floor (for guests) of the house has three bedrooms, 1.5 baths (one bath/shower with sink and toilet- the half bath has only toilet and sink), a large fully equipped kitchen, a dining room that seats 8, and a comfortable living room. Bedroom 1 has a queen bed and opens onto a back deck that descends into a shared garden. Bedroom 2 has a full bed and a window tha
neighborhood_overview:
Conveniently located and in walking distance to 24th st Station BART, Castro, Dolores Park, Noe Valley, and Potrero Hill. Walking score of 98 because of the variety of great restaurants, cafe's and shopping opportunities. Just around the corner: Dynamo Donuts, St. Francis Creamery, Salumeria, Haus, Wise Sons Deli, Flour and Water, Heath Tile, Aperto, Chez Mama, El Metate, Sightglass, Philz Coffee, Bar Tartine and more. There are also many nightspots nearby.

For people with children, there are more than 8 parks within a half mile many of them with climbing structures or just some room to run around.
host_about:
I am a retired, former teacher from the midwest. I moved out to California to be closer to my grandchildren who also live in the Mission. I love coffee and dining out and I am happy to give you a list of neighborhood eateries and cafes. 

5 things I can't live without:  My 4 grandkids and the Economist. 

I am new to hosting on AirBnB, but have a lifetime of hosting guests (friends, family, friends of friends, etc.) Though I keep to myself as I have my own separate master suite with a private entrance, I am more than happy to help out. Just let me know what you need to make your stay GREAT!

Languages: I speak only English, but my daughter assists me with the AirBnB bookings and preparations. She speaks English, French and Spanish.

name: Beautiful Apartment with Green views
description:
A true retreat to relax in.
Comfortably sleep on memory-foam mattresses and a sofabed.
Enjoy our large 52" TV + chromecast and share our WIFI.
Grand View park nearby provides breathtaking views. Walk downhill to Golden Gate Park and plenty of restaurants etc.

Our apartment faces a tranquil large backyard surrounded by trees and it is accessed thru our garage area.
Space includes 1 bedroom, 1 den/bedrom (w/ curtains for privacy, no door), living room + kitchenette area w/ small dining table.

The space
Modern & comfortable, bright & airy. Both the bedroom and den have queen size memory-foam beds. The den acts like a bedroom with a large closet, no door or window, and a thick curtain provides privacy. The living area has a large TV, sofabed, and a window with view of the large backyard.

The kitchen has all the appliances needed: electric kettle, coffee-maker, full-size fridge, microwave, small toaster oven, and stove. The
neighborhood_overview:
You will love this Inner Sunset/Golden Gate Heights neighborhood with super easy access to the prime attractions inside the Golden Gate Park.

5min drive or 10min walk downhill to 9th & Irving business district of the Inner Sunset, which has several distinctive bars, restaurants, coffee shops, boutiques, grocery shopping, nail/hair salons, and other conveniences. Also easy access to West Portal which offers more of the same.

6min drive or 15min walk to Golden Gate Park and its main attractions, i.e. the California Academy of Sciences, Japanese Tea Garden, DeYoung Art Museum, Music Concourse, SF Botanical Garden.

5min drive or 19min walk to UCSF Campus/Medical Center, the premier teaching hospital in the nation.

7min walk up Moraga street is Grandview Park, where sunset views are breathtaking (check yelp listing), and stairs provide for some good exercise. You can soak in 360 degree views at the top with views of the Pacific Ocean, Golden Ga
host_about:
Hi fellow travelers,

Like you, we love globe-trotting! Born in one continent, living in another and pleasure-traveling all over, San Francisco is our favorite city, and our home for past 17 years.

Hosting guests is a labor of love, we want to share and spread positivity that we desire ourselves. Count on us to be prompt & helpful, and don't expect to hear about Fishermen's wharf on my list of suggested must-see places :)

Life is not meant to be lived in one place, lets go somewhere!

name: Modern, Luxury 2BR/2BA New Backyard *Now Open!*
description:
A cheery, cozy, oceanview retreat near restaurants, shopping, and public transport. Many consider our place to be a great refuge since we are a little further away from downtown. Sleeps 2-4 (1 full-sized bed in BR #1. 2 sofa beds in BR #2/living room with TV and Netflix). Located in the residential Parkside/Sunset area, we're steps from the MUNI rail that gets you downtown in 25-30 min. See Other Things to Note before booking. 15-20 minutes from SFO & downtown by car. Free street parking.

The space
Enjoy this new, modern apartment just steps away to public transport, restaurants, and shops. We are near the Zoo, Ocean Beach, free concerts in Stern Grove in the summer, produce markets, delicatessen, butcher, and laundromats. We have ocean views and a sitting area in the garden. 25-30 minutes to downtown by public transport.

Upon entry to the right you'll find the first bath with dual vanity sinks, dual head shower including a Rainshower head, and toilet
neighborhood_overview:
The Parkside area located in the west side of San Francisco has a very laid back vibe with the L-Taraval MUNI line providing convenient access to downtown, many tourist attractions and local hangouts.

Walk to restaurants, shops, and parks. Korean, Japanese, Thai, Italian, Shabu Shabu (Asian fondue), American, Chinese, Seafood, and dumpling restaurants just steps away. McCoppin Square with playground and Stern Grove Park are within walking distance as well. Less than 5 minutes by car enjoy wine tasting most Saturdays and Sundays at a local wine shop.

Get downtown using public transport within 20-30 minutes without the worry of costly parking. Enjoy Ocean Beach and the Zoo, or visit neighboring West Portal or the Inner Sunset district and Golden Gate Park. Lots to see and do!

#29 and #66 buses are also within a few minutes away by foot and provide access to Golden Gate Park. There, enjoy the Conservatory of Flowers, the DeYoung Museum, The California A
host_about:
Hello! My name is Kesinee. Pictured above is my family. I speak Thai and very limited Spanish, my husband speaks a little French, and my kids speak Chinese (Cantonese and some Mandarin) and some Thai. We love to travel, we love San Francisco, and we love skiing, camping, and hiking. 

My husband, who is a data scientist, enjoys roasting coffee and building electric bikes which we like to use instead of cars whenever possible. I am from Brooklyn, New York, have lived on both the East and West Coasts in the United States as well as in the South and Southeast. I also lived and worked in Thailand for some time.

We enjoy meeting wonderful folks from all around the world near and far. We look forward to hosting you!

name: Sunny Potrero Hill Cottage
description:
This comfortable one bedroom home located in sunny Potrero Hill (best weather in the city) has a queen size bed, wifi, cable TV, is close to the 101 and 280 freeways, and is a convenient minute walk to Caltrain and SF Muni.
In addition, the common room has a queen size sofa bed and a full size fold down sofa/futon.

The space
This is a quirky, lovable little cottage. Pictures are slightly outdated and will be updated soon but show part of the space in a 'work in progress' status.

Guest access
Guests have, unless otherwise agreed upon, full access to the front house with the exception of the attic space and basement.

License number
STR-0001920
host_about:
Hi, I'm Ed. I have a great job working as an analyst for a major wine and spirits producer, here in San Francisco. Aside from raindrops on roses and whiskers on kittens a few of my favorite things are my wonderful dog, Darla, my family,  sports (participating as well as spectating), exploring new places and seeing new things, and movies --preferably good ones, of course. 

I live on the property but not in the main house itself. There is a small mother-in-law cottage in the back with plumbing and a side entrance, so there is no need to enter the main house. Hopefully, this means travelers have the best of both worlds, i.e. you have someone close by who can address emergencies, answer questions, and make sure all your lodging needs are met while at the same you have complete run of the house with complete privacy. 

Darla and I look forward to meeting you in person!

name: Comfortable Artistic Condo
description:
Comfortable and eclectic two-bedroom, one bathroom apartment. 25% discount for reservations longer than one month. Walking distance from the artistic hub of the City (SF Symphony, Ballet, Opera, SF Jazz). Hip restaurants and shopping in the Mission and Hayes Valley districts. 5 minute walk to Dolores park, 15 minute walk to the Castro and the City's center, 40 minute walk to Ferry Building/Embarcadero/Yerba Buena Gardens.

The space
SAN FRANCISCO SHORT-TERM RESIDENTIAL RENTAL REGISTRATION NUMBER STR- (phone number hidden). The apartment's environment is unpretentious, comfortable, aesthetically fun and eclectic. If you are a musician you have access to a baby grand piano. If you need a little bit of green in an urban environment the back room's window looks upon a funky group of plants. The bed sleeps one person comfortably and accommodates two. The front bedroom(when available) has a super comfy mattress and sleeps two. There is a TV and DVD player to watch mo
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in the extremely central Mission Dolores neighborhood at the intersection of multiple transportation hubs. The city's center (Union Square, shopping malls etc) is 20 mins walking distance on Market Street, which connects City Hall to the Embarcadero. It is walking distance to the exquisite cultural offerings of San Francisco, just steps from the Civic Center Arts Corridor: SF JAZZ, SF Ballet, SF Opera, Asian Art Museum, SF Public Library, City Hall and SF Arts Commission Gallery, New Conservatory Theater, Conservatory of Music. The Mission Dolores neighborhood is a vibrant neighborhood providing alternative shopping and is a heaven for foodies. You can find everything from street food to exquisite gourmet food. Dolores Park is three blocks away, you can hop on the J Church and get to Noe Valley in a sec, walking distance from Hayes Valley, the Castro and SOMA.
host_about: I am an artist and educator with over twenty years living and working in San Francisco.  Languages spoken include English, Spanish and Greek and I have fun challenging myself with communication in French.  I am a proud San Franciscan and love San Francisco's multicultural, cosmopolitan and artistic character.

name: Cute part of the city near Bart
description:
Private room in a 3 bedroom in-law apartment with a door to the backyard/garden, in a quiet part of town. Two other girls in their 20's live at the apartment. This is my permanent residence but I travel a lot and rent it out when I do :)

The space
This particular bedroom is located downstairs next to one of two other bedrooms. There is a door with a window that leads to an outdoor space with a garden. The room is super quiet and cozy. My decor is bohemian/Asian inspired. A lot of good energy in the house.

Guest access
The backyard area is communal and so it the garage/storage area. Not a whole lot of room there but if you need to store some items feel free. The washer and dryer is free and used by both upstairs and downstairs tenants. There is one bathroom with a shower and tub and is for the house to use. Same goes for the kitchen and eat-in space. The other roommates should be around, but they are both super cool. We just ask for everyone
neighborhood_overview: Glen Park is a cute, quiet neighborhood located near the more southern part of the city. There are a lot of cute coffee shops, restaurants and local businesses a few blocks near the BART station. Glen Park Canyon is a great walk/hike where you don't feel like you're in the city anymore. Awesome route for jogging. We live very close to the Mission which is also a great neighborhood.
host_about: Grad school student, seeking masters in Acupuncture and Oriental Medicine. California raised, currently living in the Seattle area. I love traveling, yoga, small dogs and outer space.

Located on a private lane on Nob Hill

Secluded outdoor garden patio for lunch on a sunny afternoon

Walk score of 96! Public transit of 100! Buses and Cable Car at the corner

Convenient location to in the middle of SF, close to all SF sites. Chinatown, North Beach, Financial District, Union Square, and transit hub

This a Non Smoking property as is all pubic areas in the city. If you must smoke you must head out to Sacramento Street

The space
Prospective guests:

Please read the 'Entire Listing' before booking. Thank you for looking.

Kitchenette area, cozy living room, bedroom and dining room, plus outdoor patio, make this place complete! Has great heating but no A/C.

Guest access

neighborhood_overview:
Nob Hill is one of San Francisco's original "Seven Hills." Which became a fashionable affluent district with the invention of the cable car. Today it is
a lively area of upscale hotels & restaurants with large young urban professional population, centered between Financial District, Union Square, Chinatown and North Beach

Restaurants near by there are just toooo many... A couple of favorites: Nob Hill Cafe at Taylor/Sacramento, Milano at Pacific/Hyde, Hyde Street Seafood at Hyde/Pacific, Rue Le Pic at Mason/Pine..... See house manual for many more ideas. I am getting hungry just thinking about it...
host_about:

name: Bernal Heights Nest -Top Location!-
description:
Take in amazing views of San Francisco and the Bay from the top of Bernal Hill at this cozy apartment just steps from the park. The location of this 1 BR guest suite/apartment is impossible to beat. Bernal Heights boasts one of the best views of the San Francisco skyline and incomparable village charm. Easy access to much of the city (~3 mi/5km from downtown), but away from the bustle, this is the perfect jump-off spot for an unforgettable SF visit!
Vaccinated guests/requests only s.v.p.!

The space
Our cozy Bernal Heights Nest is equipped with everything you might need during a visit to San Francisco. It's perfect for travelers, weekend getaways, business trips, etc...

Access to a refrigerator, toaster oven, microwave oven, coffee maker, and electric kettle. The bed is a Queen murphy bed. Flatscreen TV & Blu-ray/DVD player with internet access/streaming capability. Small DVD library available upon request.

Guest access
The
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood of Bernal Heights is built around Bernal Hill and the apartment is located just steps from the park. A short walk away, on Cortland Ave., you will find boutique stores, the Good Life Grocery, the Bernal Heights library, artisan bakeries, restaurants, bars, cafes, etc. . . Safeway and Walgreen's are also less than a mile away.
host_about:
We are a well-traveled couple, one a San Francisco born and bred native, the other a European transplant who's called the city home for the past 15+ years, who love living in San Francisco, the Bay Area and Northern California. 
Between the two of us we've been fortunate to have visited upwards of 60 countries ourselves and we appreciate your desire to experience a destination from a more local perspective. 
We look forward to hosting you!

name: Elegant Union Square hotel room
description:
The Club Donatello is a four-star, Gold Crown, boutique timeshare providing full upscale hotel services. It embraces an intimate ambiance enhanced by the 15th floor clubroom w/hot tub and open air balcony. It's ideally located at Mason and Post, a single block from the cable car, SF's famous Union Square (billed as "Crown Jewel of Shopping Districts" ), the theatre district, the Olympic Club and a plethora of art galleries. China Town is a six block walk. In/out covered parking is available.

The space
Club DonatelloÃ¢â¬â¢s luxuriously appointed rooms occupy floors 11, 12, and 14 (top three floors) and are complete with original art, classic furnishings, custom terrycloth robes, entertainment center, and mini-bar. The 45 large 400 square foot hotel style rooms, have two double beds with comfortable mattresses and 600 thread count sheets plus a queen sized sleeper sofa (the two double beds can occasional be replaced with a single king sized bed given advanced notic
neighborhood_overview:
The Donatello Hotel is perfectly located one block from Union Square with fine restaurants, museums, the Moscone Center, the Geary Street theater district, and a wide variety of shopping experiences all close by. ACT (American Conservative Theater) is virtually 100 yards down Mason street.
Unlike most SF hotels, Club Donatello's location is very convenient for a mid-afternoon refresher between the days activities and dining out or to just drop off packages.
host_about:
Meimei and  Lynn, have been married for 39 years and it looks almost certain that they will reach 40.  His job security is assured by his delivering excellent coffee to his wife every morning.  
     Lynn is an over-educated out-of-date engineer so he retired early.  Meimei, not wanting to be left behind, followed suit and retired from business management.  Now she paints, fixes their computers, takes classes, and tries to keeps  track of their five daughters.  He writes books (Surviving Five Daughters), handles their retirement including AirBnB, and adores his wife.  At one time or another they have lived, together or separately, in Ohio, Minnesota, Massachusetts, New York, the Marshall Islands, Paris, Colorado, and Northern California.

name: Gorgeous large 3BR steps to Dolores Park!
description:
Location! Location! Location! Our sunny well-lit home is on the most desirable block of the hip Mission district - the best local restaurants, bars & Dolores Park around the corner. Steps to Tartine, Delfina, Bi-Rite.

Beautifully designed with all modern amenities & well-stocked kitchen. Comfortable beds, HD-TV, Bath linens, potential free parking and more!

Easy access to downtown, Moscone and other tourist spots with the charm of a San Francisco local neighborhood.

The space
Our home is a beautiful well lit condo in the heart of the hip Mission-Dolores neighborhood, steps to Dolores Park - a hot spot where SF locals like to hang out. We're also steps away from the Valencia corridor, where Michelin starred restaurants share the block with world-class local cafes and taquerias serving delicious tacos and burritos - yum!

Ideal for folks who're moving to San Francisco, for a temporary stay while you figure out your living arrangeme
neighborhood_overview:
Wow! where do i start. Our neighborhood is a treasure trove of what makes San Francisco special.

We are steps from the Dolores park. The Dolores Park is a central hub for locals to hangout it. Weekdays or weekends you will find it filled with people from all over, very much a colorful tapestry that makes San Francisco special.

The Dolores Park Cafe is wonderful for coffee, breakfast and lunches. Right next door to our place is Delfina, one of SF's best restaurants and pizzeria (serves excellent Italian style pizza). There is the Tartine Bakery on the other corner that has incredible baked goodies, and Chad Robertson's incredible bread. Widely acclaimed as the best ice cream west of the Mississippi, the Bi-Rite ice cream shop is a must try (and about 30 steps from our home). The Bi-Rite market has local organic fruits , vegetables and other groceries that can help with planning meals if you'd like to cook. A block away is the Valencia corridor, home to multiple Mi
host_about:
We're avid travelers. Small sampling of trips we've taken over the last two years: Barrow and Coldfoot Camp in Alaska (last winter), Australia, New Zealand, Aitutaki in the Cook Islands, Hawaii, Dubai, New York City, Vermont, India.

We love exploring different cultures and sampling local cuisines. Good food from a hole-in-the-wall is much preferred to bland touristy fare from sit down places :)

name: Classic Car Room ~ Excelsior Dist.
description:
My house is very tranquil and neat, this is a quiet neighborhood.

The Mission, with all it's interesting restaurants, is just a bus ride away.

The space
My house is very tranquil and neat, this is a quiet neighborhood.
Aside from it being quiet it has a wonderful view of the city. :)
This is a smaller home so I think when you arrive you should see it as your home. I ask that shoes be left at the door. I have slippers for use.
It is more relaxing that way.

FROM/TO SFO AIRPORT: Twenty minutes from SFO by car and 25 minutes by BART. Shuttles cost about $30 to $35, if you prefer that a driver pick you up. BART is least expensive and second fastest way to get from airport to my place.
There is a bus #44 at the BART station you can take to my place. It stops at the bottom of my street.

TRANSPORTATION: The Glen Park BART station is about an 10-minute walk from here and, within the City boundaries. A Clipper Card
neighborhood_overview:
The house is in a quiet neighborhood.... very diverse.
It is called the Excelsior/Mission area of the city.
host_about: I am a vivacious and happy woman. I travel, and keep busy with classic car shows.. I am also involved fundraising car shows. I now have the time and space to host fellow travelers in my home which keeps me very busy. And it's a really nice way meeting people from all over the world.  I worked at the  San Francisco Symphony for 31 years which is where I retired from. A friend mentioned Airbnb for something to keep me busy being retired now.

Laundry, wifi and much more included.

neighborhood_overview: The Divisidero corridor is the center of it all these days in San Francisco! New restaurants are opening all the time, and you are close to all sorts of great stuff to eat, buy and do. Served by several bus lines to get you downtown or out towards Golden Gate Park and the ocean, you are a short, interesting walk to the Haight and much more. It's also the actual geographic center of the city, which is pretty cool, and still has the largest concentration of original Victorian homes in the city. No matter where you walk or what you do, you can't help but have a great time.

Although it is not walking distance to the top tourist attractions, it is a very quiet and safe neighborhood, perfect for relaxing a long day of walking. It is about a 5 minute walk from the popular West Portal area, well known for it's excellent neighborhood restaurants, bars and boutiques.

We enjoy family and friends with strong ties to our community, we have traveled the world developing relationships throughout. Our interests are laughter, live entertainment, music, culture, the arts, sport, animals & cuisines from all around the world.

My wife is from France, and we have traveled to Germany, Holland, Greece, Mexico, Jamaica, Hawaii, Puerto Rico, Bahamas, Italy and look forward to much more someday. 

While traveling we enjoy immersing ourselves in the local fabric of the destinations and what they have to offer. We are friendly clean and take care to be conscientious of our surroundings and hope to have the same in our home.

Beautiful 1-bedroom in-law apartment with private entrance in quiet SF area. Premium cable, internet and outdoor area. Easy parking. Quick access to freeways and public transportation. Small to medium size pets welcome.

Newly rennovated large 1-bedroom private in-law with kitchenette including stovetop, convection oven and small refrigerator/freezer. Eat-in kitchen. Comfortable seating area. name: Welcome to the Edge of the Earth!
description:
Come stay with us at the edge of the Earth! Only 7 blocks from the beach, this quiet, private in-law apartment is ready for guests. Perfect for families, we're five blocks from the SF Zoo and three blocks from the L-Taraval train. Our three-room space is spacious, clean and quiet. You're also welcome to borrow our SF Zoo passes for the day.

The space
Our open concept (read: no doors!) three room in-law is a great space for families and friends traveling to San Francisco. A well-appointed bathroom (with door) is adjacent to the main bedroom, with a very comfortable queen bed. The second bedroom has a queen-sized sleeper sofa. A kitchenette is included in the common third room. The kitchenette DOES NOT HAVE AN OVEN, but includes a microwave, hot plate, small refrigerator, coffee maker, dishes and silverware for 6. A local market is on the corner, making shopping a breeze!
** Please Note: Smoking is strictly prohibited on the property, including the back yard
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood has lots to offer: we're five blocks from the San Francisco Zoo, seven blocks from the beach, and only three blocks from the train which can take you to all the local tourist spots within the hour. We have a few great restaurants, coffee shops and local businesses to share with you as well!
host_about: We're a fun, low-key family in the Outer Sunset neighborhood of San Francisco.  We have two daughters, 8 and 4. We live upstairs from the apartment and enjoy meeting travellers from around the world!

name: Dreamy Centrally Located Home with Choice of Outside Space
description:
I poured my heart and soul getting this house perfect. Stepping inside you will be surrounded by both modern and european classic decor. Fully renovated, professionally decorated, this is three stories of luxurious relaxation.

Three separate bedrooms. Master Bedroom has a king bed, 2nd Bedroom has a queen bed and 3rd bed has a trundle bed with two single twin beds.

Some of the amenities include:
Super fast wifi
Washer / Dryer
Free garage parking (although we recommend that you don't rent a car. Our location is perfect for walking and/or taking public transportation and/or uber and lyft).
Full kitchen with modern appliances, silverware etc.

Guests will have access to the entire 3 bedroom home including all of the amenities like the washer and dryer and free parking.

Complete privacy unless you need anything. Then we're just a phone call away.

Located in popularJazz Fillmore district, the house is very central.
neighborhood_overview: Located in popularJazz Fillmore district, the house is very central. It's walking distance to Alamo Square (with the Painted Ladies), Japantown, and Hayes Valley. Just a few blocks away are some of San Francisco's best restaurants and nightlife.
host_about: Gorgeous San Fran is my home base but my business and work take me all over the world.  Wouldn't you know it, after finally getting my home perfect I get the call that I'm off to another market indefinitely.  I'm back and forth but there's nothing like being at home.  I'm pretty picky so I'm hoping you find my home to be as comfortable as I do!

name: Renovated 1930s Home with Lush Garden
description:
As you arrive through your private entry, you will proceed upstairs to your living quarters. There, youÃ¢â¬â¢ll find a bright, spacious living room with beautiful wood floors and the original period fireplace.

The adjacent dining room comfortably seats six if you wish to dine in. The well-equipped kitchen is next to the dining room with an adjoining, cozy breakfast nook. You can enjoy your morning coffee overlooking the garden area. If you wish to have afternoon tea there, you may spot hummingbirds swaying in the breeze on the princess flower tree right outside the nook window.

Both bedrooms have comfortable queen size beds with hypoallergenic bedding. One bedroom has a delightful sitting area, while the other bedroom has a well-loved antique desk.

description:
One friendly dog lives in the house.
My place is away from the noise, pollution and hustle of downtown. You will sleep well, and may wake up to birdsong. Your private bathroom has a walk in shower, large tub and partial view of the bay. It's convenient for the airport, has easy parking and you can be downtown in 15-20 minutes. You will enjoy beautiful views and a very friendly host. We welcome well behaved children.

The space
My family home was designed by local artists. From the antique-car-hood awning to the San Francisco Hyde Street Cable Car cable railing in the stairs, every feature is unique. High ceilings, walls of windows, and broad open spaces give this house a light and open spacious feel and panoramic view of the city rare in a town where space tends to run sparse.

The room has an antique queen four poster bed, with memory foam matress, and a regular queen bed.

My home is best for visitors with a car, or using Uber, Lyft or T
neighborhood_overview:
The Bayview has until recently, been the best-kept (and sunniest) secret of San Francisco. We are in the very southeast corner of the city, an area that is rapidly transforming with new residential developments.

All kinds of little gems are flourishing in our neighborhood as the rest of the city catches on to the great potential of this side of town. Flora Grubb Nursery and Cafe, San Francisco Mead Company, and Old School Cafe are a few local businesses I'd recommend checking out.

Our street has a tight-knit community of families who are very active in local affairs. There is a beehive in the community garden immediately opposite our house.
host_about: I am a techie who understands that people and relationships are the most important thing in life. I am humbled every day by the lessons I learn from those around me. I am blessed to exercise and spend time in natural beauty regularly.

neighborhood_overview:
Neighborhood
Noe Valley

Where do San Francisco hipsters move when they grow up? Noe Valley. This small enclave nestled in the hills above San Francisco Bay is proof positive you don't have to leave the city when you transition from Stoli to stroller. In fact, Noe Valley is now the city's most coveted neighborhood in SF.

Jaw-dropping views of the bay looking east toward Oakland greet you from almost any street corner. Boutiques are chockablock here. With bakeries like Noe Valley Baking Company and restaurants that have become beloved neighborhood institutions, like Firefly, Noe Valley is paradise for foodies. Thanks to the Noe Valley Farmers market on Saturdays, locals never have to leave the neighborhood to get their fix of fresh organic vegetables, fruit and honey.

Some of the best public schools in the city are here in Noe Valley. Fairmount Elementary School and Alvarado Elementary School are both notable for their levels of family involvement.

Quiet and comfortable guest suite in rear of gorgeous Potrero Hill condo. Private entrance, private bath, private outdoor deck with stunning views of the city. Firm California King bed, Desk with Chair, and TV with Netflix! & HBO Max. Includes: towels, bedding, toiletries, microwave, fridge (no full kitchen), and filtered water.
Note: we will be updating photos shortly to reflect new Persian rugs and a leather chair that was just added for comfort / coziness.

The space
Very private, comfortable, and quiet room with California king bed in gorgeous condo. Includes private entrance, private bathroom with shower, access to shared deck with stunning views. Microwave, mini fridge, TV, wi-fi included.

Close to SFO, downtown, Mission and Dogpatch districts; public transportation extremely accessible. Ideal home base for anyone visiting or working in San Francisco.

Walk score of 93, 1-2 blocks from shops, organic groceries, library, cafes, re
neighborhood_overview:
Potrero Hill is one of the most desirable neighborhoods in the city because of its central location and stunning views. Our neighborhood is extremely quiet, family oriented, and has tons of wonderful local businesses to support! Since we are on the West side of San Francisco, we also experience the sunniest and warmest weather In the city.

We live on a very quiet block, 1-2 blocks from: the library, cafes, restaurants, organic/local groceries, charming shops. Walk score: 93.

Super accessible to downtown and Mission districts (Both a 12-15 minute bus ride) and the Dogpatch (10 minute walk).

name: Elegant One Bedroom Edwardian on Nob Hill.
description:
Elegant one bedroom Edwardian with crown molding and period details in the heart of Nob Hill. Two blocks from Grace Cathedral this is the genuine Nob Hill with great access to transportation, restaurants and grocery. Stunning roof deck with BBQ and views of the Golden Gate Bridge. Decor is a refined combination of modern and antiques. Live like a true San Franciscan in the heart of one of her finest neighborhoods!

The space
We spent a great deal of effort filling the apartment with charming items like real oriental rugs, charming antiques and a comfortable (upgraded) sofa bed mattress.

Guest access
You will have access to the roof deck, apartment and laundry room in the basement.

Other things to note

name: Great Cozy Home in Sunset District
description:
We offer our entire 2 bed 1 bath ground level unit in the Sunset Area. 1 block from the L metro light rail/subway car that takes aprox. 25 mins to Downtown/Moscone Center without traffic! Close to restaurants, supermarkets, GG Park, Zoo, Ocean Beach, USF, UCSF, SFSU. Plenty of free street parking. Elegantly and efficiently furnished with sofas, TVs, and work spaces (perfect for business travelers). Spacious kitchen/dining area. Great value for location! Please carefully review house rules.

The space
-Kitchen/dining area with toaster oven, cooktop, refrigerator, microwave, coffee machine, rice cooker, electric kettle
-Queen sized bed in each bedroom with memory foam mattress
-Workspaces - desk and chair in each bedroom
-Smart TVs with over the air digital channels
-Ground-level - no stairs
-Snacks

To make best use of the space there is NO living room. The kitchen/dining area is the common space for guests.

Gues
neighborhood_overview:
One of the quieter areas in San Francisco. One block from restaurants, coffee shops and two blocks from laundry service if needed.

For business travelers: Even though the distance might look further away from downtown than other neighborhoods, the key is the Muni L light rail. Since it is the direct route from the property, it takes approximately 30 mins to downtown in the subway system. It may take a bit longer during rush hour.
host_about: I am a working professional living in San Francisco. I love this city and would like to help everyone make a memorable trip here.   Our space is licensed and permitted in the city of San Francisco.  My wife Ban helps with hosting to assist you with your stay.

name: Bernal Heights North Slope 2 BR Charmer
description:
Location, location, location! Situated in one of the most desirable neighborhoods in San Francisco this bohemian apartment has a rustic charm provided by downtown views and a secluded deck and garden. Eclectic furnishings and artworks provide the apartment with a one of a kind aesthetic set against an urban San Francisco setting.

The space
Located on the sunny north slope of Bernal Hill, this apartment is ideally located. Close to all the action yet safe and secluded. The interior has recessed lighting, laminate and hardwood flooring and is fully furnished and equipped. The space feels cozy and welcoming and provides great views of the city. The interior is comprised of furnishings and artworks collected over the years from many parts of the globe and local artists. This space is on the ground level facing the garden with a real, local and lived in ambience.

Guest access
Guests can access the laundry unit in the garage. There is also an iro
neighborhood_overview: Bernal heights is a truly charming neighborhood with a village like quality. An interesting mix of Victorian and modern architecture. There are many walks up winding staircases, through community gardens, to Bernal Hill. Precita Park is a few blocks away with its mural arts centre and evident murals and is adjacent to the Mission District known for its restaurants, bars and clubs. Being a foodie town there are a wide range of options close by, from a multitude of taquerias and cheap eats to world renowned restaurants. The neighborhood remains safe and quiet whilst being a hop, skip and jump away from the liveliest spots.
host_about: I have traveled extensively throughout my life and have an affinity for travelers and an experiential understanding of what's involved when we uproot and relocate our lives. I have met some great people through hosting and enjoy welcoming guests from all parts of the world and all walks of life.

name: Sunny Bernal Heights Casita with Private Entrance
description:
This Bernal Heights casita is a completely remodeled and updated early 20th Century carriage house. A 200+ sq ft, 2-room studio with its own private bathroom, kitchen, and entrance from the street. Situated on the sunny, quiet north slope of Bernal Heights, we are walking distance from Precita Park, Cortland Street, Mission District, SF General Hospital, and the top of Bernal Hill which boasts some of the best views of San Francisco. Steps away from Downtown/Financial District bus line.

The space
This is the perfect San Francisco getaway! You will feel like you are living in the country while in the midst of the hustle and bustle of the City.

2 room guest suite/studio with plenty of natural light and a queen sized bed. Fully equipped kitchen with granite counter tops. Hardwood floors throughout. Wall heater and portable heater available. Updated bathroom with shower stall and new ventilation system. TV and internet access available.

S
neighborhood_overview: The North Slope of Bernal Heights is the closest thing to country-living in the midst of the hustle and bustle of the big City.  Quiet, peaceful, friendly, sunny, and also boasting some of the best views of San Francisco.  Peralta Park is steps away from the casita, and it offers you a chance to take a break, sit in cement blocks, and marvel at the expansive San Francisco skyline.  Take a hike further up the hill using the staircase walk and reach the top of Bernal Hill....here the 360 degree views of the San Francisco Peninsula are unmatched!  DonÃ¢â¬â¢t miss the tree swing at the top of the hill.  Restaurants are all around you...the closest are Precita Park Cafe, Los Yaquis, CharlieÃ¢â¬â¢s Cafe, and Doma.  Take a 10-15 minute walk down the hill to partake in all the restaurant options available in the Mission. host_about:
Welcome to Bed|n|Build! Bed|n|Build provides a landing pad for entrepreneurs, designers, coders, engineers and other innovators and builders from the broader startup community.

When staying with us, you'll meet like-minded individuals with a culture of pragmatic cooperation and collaboration. We are more than just about housing. We care, build trusted relationships, and support each other in achieving our goals and startup visions. 

We offer private and shared bedrooms that allow even bootstrapping founders to live in a great neighborhood and the friendly, clean, convenient, and safe place they deserve.

Don't reach out if others have described you as picky, high maintenance, or a drama king or queen. Also, do not contact us if you are not interested in getting to know the other builders sharing the house or joining the Happy Hours that we organize for the community occasionally.

Watch the sun set into the ocean from the deck area, revealing the city lights at night. This ground floor guest suite boasts a feeling of space with wooden flooring, stylish furnishings, and a statement fireplace in the living area.

neighborhood_overview:
There's hardly a neighborhood that compares with Russian Hill, with its mesmerizing views, heart-stopping hairpin turns, and sheer historical grandeur.

host_about:
Welcome to Bed|n|Build! Bed|n|Build provides a landing pad for entrepreneurs, designers, coders, engineers and other innovators and builders from the broader startup community.

When staying with us, you'll meet like-minded individuals with a culture of pragmatic cooperation and collaboration. We are more than just about housing. We care, build trusted relationships, and support each other in achieving our goals and startup visions. 

We offer private and shared bedrooms that allow even bootstrapping founders to live in a great neighborhood and the friendly, clean, convenient, and safe place they deserve. 

We partner with startup accelerators, bootcamps, coding academies, and co-working spaces and prefer recruiting our residents through peer-recommendations and our networks. So please let us know how you have heard from us.

I am also an entrepreneur and builder who now runs an international startup accelerator out of Palo Alto, SF, and NYC. When I bring founders from abroad, one of the hardest challenges for them is to find appropriate housing. That's why I stepped up and created Bed|n|Build.

We love social, easy going, and low maintenance folks. After all, it's a co-living place with diverse people from the different corners of this world. Nerdy - sure. Geeky - also welcome. 

Don't reach out if others have described you as picky, high maintenance, or a drama king or queen. Also, do not contact us if you are not interested in getting to know the other builders sharing the house or joining the Happy Hours that we organize for the community occasionally.

name: The Guest Suite, a Romantic Garden Retreat in NOPA
description:
The Guest Suite, in the geographical heart of the city, is convenient for traveling to all parts of San Francisco. Served by 5 bus lines, our guests can be downtown in 10 minutes. We are 5 minutes by bus to the Castro, Haight Ashbury, and Golden Gate Park, 10 to Noe Valley and the Mission, in NOPA, a destination in itself. People may call it Ã¢â¬ÅtrendyÃ¢â¬Â, but you can call it home.

We love our city, but do travel ourselves, so we hope to please our guests in many small ways. Let us surprise you.

The space
We designed our space with more luxury than expected from a short term rental, because we built this for our own use. We offer 540 thread count sheets, down pillows on request, extra blankets and throws, and plush 100% cotton bath towels. Guests are provided with the use of fine china, more than ample numbers of utensils, wine and regular glasses, as well as over a dozen mugs for freshly roasted coffee and a large assortment of teas. The art relates to
neighborhood_overview: We are a lively neighborhood surrounded by excellent restaurants and services on the Divisadero Corridor 2 blocks away. A laundromat is on our corner. You can find so many great places to dine, you may need a 2nd trip to try them all. You can walk to 6 coffee houses, or try French, Italian, Japanese, American, Greek, Mexican, Korean, Thai, Indian, Seafood, Wine bars, a brew pub, an Italian bar, BBQ, cafes and pizza parlors. We do not have a stove, so you have the perfect excuse not to cook! We do however have a microwave and Bi-Rite market has excellent prepared foods that can be heated in the microwave. Faletti Foods also has an exceptionally good deli, and Delissio in the same building has a good selection of prepared foods.
host_about:
My husband and I are avid travelers and spend most of that time in Europe. We are native San Franciscans and love to share our city with guests from all over the world. The Guest Suite was built for friends and family and we only started renting it as a favor to a friend who helped with the construction. It has been a great experience for us.

I love to cook and may start either an Italian cooking class or a market tour of San Francisco. I have provided informal winery tours to guests, trips to Muir Woods, and trips down the Pacific coast. All tours involve a restaurant stop. Even the Guest Suite has cookbooks about San Francisco restaurants, markets, and grocery stores. 

Thanks to our guests, we are now able to travel twice a year.

name: The Painted Man- SF Historic Victorian Mansion
description:
Please contact me before reserving. I do not accept instant bookings.

The Covid 19 pandemic has changed all of our lives. Keeping everyone free of germs at The Painted Man has always been the first priority.
Disinfecting the entire home is part of the usual cleaning routine for housekeeping prior to the Covid19 outbreak. Gloves are always worn to clean.

The space
Built in 1893 by renowned architects Keenan & Cranston(grandfather of Senator Alan Cranston), this Victorian is BROTHER to the world famous Painted Ladies 2 blocks away at Historic Alamo Square park. This well preserved 4 level Queen Ann Victorian Mansion retains its period details but is also updated with all modern amenities. Grand 3 level staircase, huge double parlors and beautiful parquet wood flooring. Total bedroom count 8 plus 4.5 baths on 4 levels. 10 beds total. More pics on F B and floor plan.

Guest access
Guest have access to all four levels.
neighborhood_overview: The Painted Man is located in the heart of the city, walkable to the city's hippest restaurants, shopping and parks, Pacific Heights, Hayes Valley, Lower Haight, Nopa, and Golden Gate park. Just steps away to many restaurants, cafes, upscale shops, and entertainment venues (SF Jazz, The Independent, The Fillmore, Symphony, Ballet, Opera. The Alamo Square neighborhood is characterized by Victorian architecture that was left largely untouched by the urban renewal projects in other parts of the Western Addition. Alamo Square Park, the neighborhood's focal point and namesake, consists of four city blocks at the top of a hill overlooking much of downtown San Francisco, with a number of large and architecturally distinctive mansions along the perimeter, including the "Painted Ladies", a well-known postcard motif.
host_about: My family has been in San Francisco since 1944. I love my home town and know it very well. I am happy and excited to share my home with guest from all over!!

host_about:
Welcome to Bed|n|Build! Bed|n|Build provides a landing pad for entrepreneurs, designers, coders, engineers and other innovators and builders from the broader startup community.

When staying with us, you'll meet like-minded individuals with a culture of pragmatic cooperation and collaboration. We are more than just about housing. We care, build trusted relationships, and support each other in achieving our goals and startup visions. 

We offer private and shared bedrooms that allow even bootstrapping founders to live in a great neighborhood and the friendly, clean, convenient, and safe place they deserve. 

We partner with startup accelerators, bootcamps, coding academies, and co-working spaces and prefer recruiting our residents through peer-recommendations and our networks. So please let us know how you have heard from us.

I am also an entrepreneur and builder who now runs an international startup accelerator out of Palo Alto, SF, and NYC. When I bring founders from abroad, one of the hardest challenges for them is to find appropriate housing. That's why I stepped up and created Bed|n|Build.

We love social, easy going, and low maintenance folks. After all, it's a co-living place with diverse people from the different corners of this world. Nerdy - sure. Geeky - also welcome. 

Don't reach out if others have described you as picky, high maintenance, or a drama king or queen. Also, do not contact us if you are not interested in getting to know the other builders sharing the house or joining the Happy Hours that we organize for the community occasionally.

description:
The perfect place to call home during your stay in San Francisco! Centrally located, whether you're coming here on business or on vacation! It is centrally located on a quiet street in the Mission / Potrero neighborhood, with many great restaurants and bars minutes from the door.

The space
***30 NIGHT MINIMUM***

This charming Mission flat is located in one of the most exciting neighborhoods in the city. This is truly a great place to stay when you come to San Francisco.

Our gorgeous, modern one-bedroom home is the perfect place for relaxing after a long day of exploring San Francisco. Being within walking distance to the heart of the vibrant Mission district makes this one of the best areas for exploring the latest San Francisco trends in restaurants, bars, shops and the general hipster scene. Great transportation links easily take y
neighborhood_overview:
The Mission District's multifarious corridors comprise an inviting melting pot of cultures, cuisines, and cool kids. Produce bins line the sidewalks in front of colorful Latino markets, and the aroma of fresh roasted coffee beans emanates from first-class cafes along this diverse neighborhoodÃ¢â¬â¢s main streets. Whether youÃ¢â¬â¢re looking for upscale restaurants, lowbrow dive bars, the best taquerias, or simply delicious street food, the Mission delivers.

Around the corner from the flat you have Blue Bottle coffee which is one of our best locally produced coffees. It shares a space with Heath Ceramics, a nationally recognized and much respected pottery business that's fun to browse. In the neighborhood itself, not only do you have many choices of delicious Mexican food, but you will find Blowfish Sushi, one of the most sought after sushi restaurants in the city. It's a fun little area to explore on foot, with some unexpected hidden gems you can stumble upon.

I look forward to seeing you in San Francisco and hope you can make this home your home-away-from-home!

neighborhood_overview:
Bernal Heights is a quaint urban oasis surrounded by San FranciscoÃ¢â¬â¢s culturally-rich and best weather neighborhoods: Mission, Potrero Hill, Noe Valley and Dogpatch. The village expresses quintessential San Francisco architecture Ã¢â¬â a mix of Edwardian homes and mid-century homes amid streets offering cool cafes, boutiques and neighborhood markets.

ItÃ¢â¬â¢s repeatedly ranked as one of the hottest S.F neighborhoods because of its warm climate, proximity to hiking trails that meander through wildflowers and grasslands on Bernal Hill and its Bay and City views.

Cortland Avenue marks the commercial heart of the neighborhood. There you'll find grocery stores and markets, delicious restaurants, bars, banks, pet stores, and more. Bernal Heights offers one of the easiest connections to the rest of the Bay, with quick access to 280, 101, BART and bike routes.

neighborhood_overview:
Hidden away in the southeastern corner of San Francisco, the quiet residential neighborhood of Portola connects to the downtown area with direct access to U.S. Route 101 and Interstate 280. Residents use these roads to travel to Downtown San Francisco and Oakland in under 25 minutes. Portola's relative obscurity has created a peaceful, close-knit community, where pastel-colored homes available for rent line the streets.

Numerous local businesses on San Bruno Avenue lie within walking distance of the neighborhoodÃ¢â¬â¢s rentals. On sunny days, many residents wind through the trails of the sprawling John McLaren Park, which borders Portola to the southwest. The park offers outdoor concerts in its Jerry Garcia Amphitheater throughout the year, where residents and visitors alike savor live music performances by a wide variety of artists.

Head up the hill to Anza St. Turn left to Sutro Park. Follow the circular path where you can get a bird's eye view of the pacific as it enters into San Francisco Bay. View Seal Rock and the Cliff House and enjoy the birds which inhabit here. You may want to continue to LandÃ¢â¬â¢s End Lookout Visitors Center.
When hiking in Golden Gate National Recreation Area, STAY on trails and keep your distance from cliffs. Extend your walk north to Lands' End trails and around wild and windy rocky cliffs with stunning views around every bend, rugged shorelines and
