Sweeping downtown views in the heart of a quiet, family neighborhood - that is what our home has to offer. You have complete access to our two bed, one bath apartment with comfortable deck. Lounge in the living room as you gaze at the city skyline, walk 10 minutes down the hill to the vibrant Mission District, or hop on the bus across the street to connect with BART and downtown. This location has it all.

The space
This is our primary home and we hope you love it as much as we do. You will see our personal collection of artwork and family photos. We welcome you as we would any guest of the family.

Guest access
Guests will be able to access the entire apartment.

License number
STR-0004148
neighborhood_overview: Walk across the street and hike to the top of the hill and you find yourself in open space with 360 degree city views. The homemade swing at the top symbolizes the friendly, creative, down to earth vibe of our community. Bernal Heights is a neighborhood of delicious moderately prices restaurants and coffee shops with food from around the world. A delightful 10 minute walk puts you on Courtland Street where you can choose Peruvian, Italian, Seafood, Sushi, Mexican, Nepalese, our own Brew Pub and more. Want to be in the heart of things? The bus stops across the street, BART is a 20 minute walk, and parking is no problem.

name: Cozy Bernal Heights Studio->Top Location!<-
description:
Located just steps from the park, take in fantastic views of San Francisco and the Bay from the top of Bernal Hill while staying at this cozy guest suite. The location is impossible to beat. Bernal Heights boasts one of the best views of the San Francisco skyline and incomparable San Francisco village charm. Easy quick access to much of the city (~3 mi/5km from downtown), but away from the bustle, this is your perfect jump-off spot for an unforgettable San Francisco visit!

License number
2022-007224STR
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood of Bernal Heights is built around Bernal Hill and the apartment is located just steps from the park. A short walk away, on Cortland Ave., you will find boutique stores, the Good Life Grocery, the Bernal Heights library, artisan bakeries, restaurants, bars, cafes, etc. . . Safeway and Walgreen's are also less than a mile away.
host_about:
We are a well-traveled couple, one a San Francisco born and bred native, the other a European transplant who's called the city home for the past 15+ years, who love living in San Francisco, the Bay Area and Northern California. 
Between the two of us we've been fortunate to have visited upwards of 60 countries ourselves and we appreciate your desire to experience a destination from a more local perspective. 
We look forward to hosting you!

description:

Enjoy four bedrooms and 4 full baths with designer finishes through-out. The stunning kitchen will please any chef with its thoughtful design and high-end appliances. neighborhood_overview: Bayview, just south of Islais Creek, is a community intent on reinventing itself as an artist's colony and gardening mecca. Both the Hunters Point Shipyard Artists Open Studio and Flora Grubb Gardens are cases in point. The neighborhood takes pride in its public and backyard gardens, and the San Francisco Produce Market provides local produce to many of San Francisco's finest restaurants. Three-quarters of the residents are loyal homeowners, many of whom have developed the Quesada Garden Initiative. This community-building effort started with a few neighbors beautifying Quesada Avenue and has blossomed into an award-winning project and serves as a model for communities across the nation. Properties are still affordable and comprised primarily of single-family residences. Architecture is a smorgasbord with some renovated projects, colorful stucco homes and Victorians.

The space

The Sunset District is San Francisco's best kept secret. It is clean and safe and quiet at night. You are about a half hour from the hustle and bustle of downtown (by car or public transport). There is a private deck and yard. It is a lovely place to relax, with a view over the Mission of downtown. There is a smart TV. Nearby are cozy cafes, unique restaurants, a park and playground and public transportation. There is easy access to the freeway.

The space
This bright and roomy studio is a comfortable space with a large north-facing glass wall with a view of downtown. The studio is on the ground floor of our house, but there are 2 steps down from the hallway to the main room of the studio. Because we live on a hill, even the ground floor has a fabulous view.

There is a comfortable queen size bed with a memory foam mattress topper, night stands and reading lights. There is a dining table with 4 chairs. A si
neighborhood_overview:
The studio is in Bernal Heights. It is on the North slope, and our home has a view over the Mission district and to Downtown.

Bernal Heights is hilly, with great views, some steep streets, stairways and tiny parks tucked into side streets. From the park at the top of our hill, about 3 blocks away, there is a 360-degree view of the City, including the bay, the Bay Bridge, the Golden Gate bridge, Twin Peaks, Downtown, Mt Diablo and south to the airport. During baseball season and at the 4th of July, fireworks are often visible from our hill.

There is another very sweet local park about 2 blocks away, perfect for kids, dogs and just strolling. There are several cafes and restaurants around the park. There is a lovely small market at the other end of the park, perfect for stocking up for a picnic.

host_about:
Hello and welcome to our home! 

We are a young married couple who met in LA during our early 20's and have lived in the Bay Area since 2011. Jenn hails from LA, the land of flip-flops and sun, and earned her undergraduate degrees and MBA from UCLA. 

Eddie spent his childhood in Michigan battling the Northern winters and perfecting his black ice driving before heading out West in search of perfect waves. He earned his undergraduate degree from Penn State and his MBA from UCLA. We both work in the tech industry. 

We have a 2-year-old bundle of joy. She's an English, Golden Retriever who will welcome you with a kisses, smiles, and a dangerous tail wag that will make you feel like a million bucks when you walk through our door.

Our weekends and getaways are likely to involve new cities, a hiking trail, or camping!

host_about:
Hi, I'm Ed. I have a great job working as an analyst for a major wine and spirits producer, here in San Francisco. Aside from raindrops on roses and whiskers on kittens a few of my favorite things are my wonderful dog, Darla, my family,  sports (participating as well as spectating), exploring new places and seeing new things, and movies --preferably good ones, of course. 

I live on the property but not in the main house itself. There is a small mother-in-law cottage in the back with plumbing and a side entrance, so there is no need to enter the main house. Hopefully, this means travelers have the best of both worlds, i.e. you have someone close by who can address emergencies, answer questions, and make sure all your lodging needs are met while at the same you have complete run of the house with complete privacy. 

Darla and I look forward to meeting you in person!

host_about: The Story of the "Sea of Love" began when Rajvi's Dream became a reality.  Having always wanted to own a second home in Southern California where two of her young adult children are attending USC (she is a Trojan too) and Rajvi has many clients, she set out to transform a run down Spanish style duplex into a beautifully restored pristine architectural gem to be shared with family and friends - new and old - from near and from far.  Growing up in West Covina, it was only apropos that this gem happened to be located on Covina Avenue.  If that wasn't enough coincidence, the property was built the year Rajvi's late mother was born. Simply stated, it was meant to be! Teaming up with brilliant Canadian born and San Francisco based architect Ian Murray and locally loved and amazingly talented general contractor Don Robinson, Rajvi set out on a renovation path that lasted nearly nine months. Darla and I look forward to meeting you in person!

name: Orange Dog Garden Studio
description:
Woodland Ave is a tranquil escape in the middle of the bustling city. Located near the eastern edge of Golden Gate Park, Orange Dog Manor is walking distance from restaurants and boutiques in every direction. One block away public transportation waits to take you anywhere you need to go. Orange Dog Manor is the perfect balance: the accessibility of the city center without the noise of a busy street.

The space
Orange Dog Manor is located on a very quiet tree lined street just steps awy from 3 very active neighborhoods. Its location allow you to have access to 4 neighborhoods and The Golden Gate park with a 5 minute walk. 4 bus lines and 1 streetcar line are 1 block from the front door allowing trips to all points of the city; public transportation at its best. The property have a secluded rear yard garden for relaxing and watching the hummingbirds. The studio is light and airy with a bank of windows to give a very open yet cozy feel.
neighborhood_overview: Orange Dog Manor is 2 blocks to Cole Valley; 2 blocks to UCSF hospital and campus and 7 blocks to the Inner Sunset.  The N-Judah streetcar is 2 blocks for the apartment.  Downtown is a 12 minute streetcar ride.  Multiple bus lines to all points in the city because of the central location. The apartment is 5 blocks to both the Golden Gate Park and the Haight- Ashbury neighborhood.

neighborhood_overview: I  love living in this neighborhood, and know that its prime location and proximity to popular landmarks, will make you fall in love with San Francisco, as much as I have. Street parking is sometimes available, but I recommend the nearby parking garages with overnight and long-term parking options low as $20/night. If you do decide to do parking on the street, please be sure to read the signs as some of the streets in the neighborhood will tow during certain days/hours of the week. Do not leave any of your personal belongings inside either in plain view or in the trunk hidden. This is a safe neighborhood, but theft tends to require citywide vigilance.
host_about:
Hey there!

I'm a Bay Area native, enjoy staying active and exploring new places with different people and cultures. I'm constantly traveling and thus welcome fellow travelers into my home, as well. 

I grew up in Oakland, which is the city just across the Bay Bridge, and went to school in Los Angeles. After obtaining my bachelor degree I moved back to the Bay Area and I have grown to love the city. A lot is in proximity and is so rich in diversity. I live in room #2 so don't be afraid to say hello and please make yourself at home.

name: Private Suite in the Heart of Parkside
description:
This is a fabulous private guest suite in the heart of the Parkside District in San Francisco. It is steps from the MUNI train that runs downtown (or out toward the beach if you'd rather) and another bus line that runs to the inner sunset, just blocks from Golden Gate Park. Great restaurants nearby include the best dumplings spot, fantastic hot pot, yummy sushi, Korean food, and our fav neighborhood restaurant/bar, the Parkside Tavern. A bit of exercise wanted? It's a lovely walk to the beach.

Guest access
you'll have a private bedroom, bathroom, living room and kitchenette! the space also has a cute entryway where you can sit to put on your shoes and its own backyard patio area with table and chairs.

Other things to note
this area around the house is walkable and safe. great restaurants all around to enjoy. i go on a 3 mile roundtrip walk to ocean beach most days of the week and the beach changes every day!

Located short walk from Lombard St., cable car turnaround, Buena Vista Cafe, coffee shops, restaurants, shopping, sightseeing, Fisherman's Wharf & Ghirardelli Square. Bedroom #1 with queen bed, smart TV, desk & views of the Golden Gate Bridge; bedroom #2 with queen bed, desk, smart TV, & walk-in closet; family room has a full sofa sleeper. Great for corporate & families alike.

The space
This spacious condominium is ideal for exploring the city, reading a good book in a cozy chase lounge in the afternoon sun, playing a board game, cards or chess; taking in view of the Golden Gate Bridge through a telescope/binoculars, or using as 2 fully functional work spaces.

neighborhood_overview: Excellent location! Two blocks from Lombard Street, a few blocks down Polk Street to the marina area where you can grab lunch and an Irish coffee at the famous Buena Vista Cafe near the cable car turnaround & chocolates at Ghirardelli Square, or a beer at SF Brewing Co. Blocks from great coffee shops, restaurants & shopping. Bike or scooter around the city using rentals located throughout the city.
host_about:
My husband, Steve and I met in our teens, married in our 20's and have 2 grown children. While my entrepreneurial husband loves to work, read, race and fly when he's not running his company, I love the outdoors, doing road trips around the US, reading, gardening, hiking, camping and decorating. 

I love sharing our home with those who enjoy cooking, visiting wineries, traveling for work & pleasure, and visiting new destinations, as well as those with family/friends in the area. 

We are available whenever necessary by phone, text or email. We are also only approximately 30-40 minute drive from the city if necessary.

Come, relax, and enjoy! If you choose to stay please don't hesitate to ask questions before your arrival, during your stay and after you have checked out. Happy travels....

Located in Central San Francisco, Orange Village Hostel is just a 5 minute walk from "Union Square". With 7 floors, the hostel is fully equipped with a kitchen, laundry room, lounge area, and free Wi-Fi accessible throughout the entire building. Stay in the center of the action in this one-of-a-kind, home away from home!

The space
The hostel is equipped with multiple room types for your traveling needs. Guests can expect private rooms to include either the option of Full size, 2x Twin size, or Queen size mattresses. Private rooms will include TV with cable access, small fridge, microwave, and the option of a full private shower, or shared hallway bathrooms.
For travelers looking for the authentic hostel experience, cheaper dorm rooms are available. Dormitory rooms can share up to 3 to 4 guests depending on choice. Bunk beds have panels installed for a bit more privacy and a small reading light, plus an outlet for your charging needs. All rooms are equipped

name: Large artistic space, epic views and easy parking
description:
The two single beds in the second bedroom are child size (suitable for people under 5ft tall only). A friendly German Shepherd dog lives on the property.
My place is away from the noise, pollution and hustle of downtown. It's convenient for the airport, has easy parking and yet you can be downtown in 15-20 minutes. You will enjoy beautiful views and a very friendly host. My place is great for families with children with a car.
Your host lives on a separate floor.

The space
My family home was designed by local artists. From the antique-car-hood awning to the San Francisco Hyde Street Cable Car cable railing in the stairs, every feature is unique. High ceilings (12ft), walls of windows, and broad open spaces give this house a light and open spacious feel and panoramic view of the city rare in a town where space tends to run sparse.

The master bedroom has a queen four poster bed, and a second queen bed. The second bedroom has a queen bed and 2 c
neighborhood_overview:
The Bayview has until recently, been the best-kept (and sunniest) secret of San Francisco. We are in the very southeast corner of the city, an area that is rapidly transforming with new residential developments.

All kinds of little gems are flourishing in our neighborhood as the rest of the city catches on to the great potential of this side of town. Flora Grubb Nursery and Cafe, San Francisco Mead Company, and Old School Cafe are a few local businesses I'd recommend checking out.

Our street has a tight-knit community of families who are very active in local affairs. There is a beehive in the community garden immediately opposite our house.
host_about: I am a techie who understands that people and relationships are the most important thing in life. I am humbled every day by the lessons I learn from those around me. I am blessed to exercise and spend time in natural beauty regularly.

name: Noe Valley/Dolores Heights Oasis, 30 Day Min.
description:
Amazing location on a quiet, family friendly block just minutes from two incredible neighborhoods, Noe Valley and the Mission. Both neighborhoods offer a plethora of great cafes, markets, shopping, the best restaurants, and nightlife right nearby. 10 minutes by foot from BART, a 12 minute walk to Whole Foods, and 15 minutes to the iconic Dolores Park. It's a quick and easy 10 minute BART ride to downtown, Union Square, and the Embarcardero.

The space
Two bedrooms, one bathroom, with the smaller bedroom doubling as a perfect work from home office. Large front patio with a picnic table, umbrella, and outdoor seating to relax and enjoy the sunny Mission/Noe weather. Smart TV and WiFi. The modern kitchen has stainless steel appliances as well a washer/dryer that you are welcome to use. There is an EcoBee thermostat with heating and fan. There is also ample closet space and storage in each of the bedrooms.

This is not a rental property, but my primary
neighborhood_overview: Beautiful, quiet street, with a lot of young families as neighbors.  Guerrero Market is a great little corner store for essentials, Chloe's cafe is a cute breakfast place a couple blocks away, and LoveJoy's Tea Room and Mr. Digby's are great spots for afternoon tea and happy hour.  Family friendly Noe Valley and the lively Mission District are both steps away, with plenty of markets, shopping, restaurants, and the best Mission taquerias, all within a 10 minute walk from the condo.
host_about: I've lived in San Francisco for the last 14 years and I'm currently renting my amazing condo in the Dolores Heights neighborhood, steps from Noe Valley and the Mission District.  I hope you enjoy my place as much as I do!

name: Cozy & Bright Apt Near Close to General Hospital
description:
This adorable garden apartment is just right for that person who loves to eat out and enjoy the City. Just outside, enjoy views of the City from this Potrero gem, one of San Francisco's sunniest neighborhoods.

The space
In this space, you have a beautiful bathroom, great living room with kitchen combo and a separate bedroom (down a few stairs) with a big closet. You'll also have access to the patio area just outside your living room door.

Other things to note
If your stay is over 6 weeks, you'll need a required cleaning every six weeks, we will include one complimentary cleaning but you will need to pay for the rest.
neighborhood_overview: The north slope of Potrero Hill is know for its sweeping views of downtown San Francisco, sunny weather (sunniest in all of San Francisco) and easy access to the best parts of town. We also have some of the City's most excellent restaurants just a block away. The neighborhood is a cool mix of homes and businesses, some warehouses, and lofts.

The newly remodeled bedroom is located in my totally remodeled 6 bedroom 6 bath unit

neighborhood_overview: I love living in this neighborhood, and know that its prime location and proximity to popular landmarks, will make you fall in love with San Francisco, as much as I have. Street parking is sometimes available, but I recommend the nearby parking garages with overnight and long-term parking options low as $20/night. If you do decide to do parking on the street, please be sure to read the signs as some of the streets in the neighborhood will tow during certain days/hours of the week. Do not leave any of your personal belongings inside either in plain view or in the trunk hidden. This is a safe neighborhood, but theft tends to require citywide vigilance.
host_about:
Hey there!

I'm a Bay Area native, enjoy staying active and exploring new places with different people and cultures. I'm constantly traveling and thus welcome fellow travelers into my home, as well. 

I grew up in Oakland, which is the city just across the Bay Bridge, and went to school in Los Angeles. After obtaining my bachelor degree I moved back to the Bay Area and I have grown to love the city. A lot is in proximity and is so rich in diversity. I live in room #2 so don't be afraid to say hello and please make yourself at home.

neighborhood_overview: I love living in this neighborhood, and know that its prime location and proximity to popular landmarks, will make you fall in love with San Francisco, as much as I have. Street parking is sometimes available, but I recommend the nearby parking garages with overnight and long-term parking options low as $20/night. If you do decide to do parking on the street, please be sure to read the signs as some of the streets in the neighborhood will tow during certain days/hours of the week. description:
Exceptional beautifully restored light-filled Victorian treasure! Top 2 floors in 2-unit bldg. Spacious 2 Bed, 2 bath urban oasis in fantastic Cole Valley/Ashbury Heights neighborhood. 1850 sq.ft. of usable space. Free garage parking spot. Quiet bldg & street in center of SF nr mass transit. Easy walk to cafes, restaurants, parks, groceries. Remodeled chef's kitchen. Upstairs views of Marin mountains and a bit of ocean and Golden Gate Bridge. No smoking. Free housekeeper every 5 wks incl

Guest access
You may park in our garage. We are centrally located and within a few blocks of a trolley line and a few bus lines. Plenty of things within walking distance. You will love this neighborhood. We are on a small one-way street in Ashbury Heights, 3 blocks from the main street of Cole Valley. We live on a peaceful, extremely walkable, green, quiet, residential street and Cole Valley has been called the friendliest neighborhood in San Francisco. Cole Valley has sev
neighborhood_overview: You will love this neighborhood.  We are on a small one-way street in Ashbury Heights, 3 blocks from the main street of Cole Valley. We live on a peaceful, extremely walkable, green, quiet, residential street and Cole Valley has been called the friendliest neighborhood in San Francisco.  Cole Valley has several restaurants and cafes, a cheese store, a bakery, two coffee shops, a hardware store, grocery store, pub, Italian wine bar and drugstore. Golden Gate Park is a 15 min walk from here and Buena Vista Park an 8 min walk.  We are also within easy walking distance to the famous Haight Street, which also has many places to shop and eat, including a great collection of vintage attire stores.
host_about: I am a University professor and my partner and co-host Dan is an artist/lawyer, and we both love travel-- we have enjoyed trips to Japan, China, Tanzania, and many parts of Europe and the UK. We are avid hikers, love cycling, and enjoy cooking and eating local, fresh foods. Our home is our peaceful retreat after exploring the city.

Noe Valley feels like a small town despite its centrality in San Francisco. host_about:
We are an adventurous, goofy and life-loving couple. We are both natives to the Bay Area, growing up in Marin and Napa counties and now calling Santa Rosa our home.

After many summers of pool parties and barbecues, we realized we'd love to open our home to visitors to the area, share our beautiful retreat with others and welcome them as we would our own family and friends. We've enjoyed Airbnb stays in our own travels and so it seems a perfect fit! 

We have both run a variety of businesses and are narrowing down our passions to make them full-time gigs. 

Janet is pursuing a career as a Pilates instructor and physical therapist, currently running the health and wellness center at UCSF working through grad school pursuing a doctorate in physical therapy. Spenser manages a multi-use events venue in San Francisco, in a free time he's building an organic vegetable garden, honing his golf game and seeking out new locales for exploring.

Together, we like to travel and meet new people, hike, cook, work in the yard, read, and play vintage video games. 

We seeks to offer an inclusive environment for all guests and welcome all people, regardless of race, religion, age, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin or disability. 

Thanks for reading our profile. We look forward to your stay! If you have any questions at all please contact us anytime :)

neighborhood_overview:
Outer Richmond is a mellow beach town that can feel worlds away from the bustling neighborhoods to the east. The district spans the western edge of the city and is sandwiched between the Presidio (national park land) to the north, Golden Gate Park to the south and with 19th Avenue acting as the arbitrary cutoff point to the East.

Previously an empty tract full of sand that ran into the ocean, the Richmond has been growing steadily for the last 100 years. It features numerous grand attractions near its edges, including China Beach, Baker Beach, the ruins of the Sutro Baths, LandsÃ¢â¬â¢ End, Sea Cliff, and the Legion of Honor.

Outer Richmond is an area that many San Francisco residents and tourists donÃ¢â¬â¢t take the time to really explore (mostly because there is so much more going on in the eastern parts of the city). But those who have visited often express their wish to hang out there more.

Unassuming ethnic restaurants can be found all over and nightlife ten

Hi, 

My name is Olivier and I want to welcome you to my home in San Francisco. I will not deny that San Francisco is probably my favorite city in the US (with Boston). I love its charming streets and colorful wall painting, the richness of its culture and the salty and always fresh sea air!

I am looking forward to hosting you and your family/ friends in this beautiful city.

name: Historic Private Penthouse
description:
Beautifully renovated upscale private penthouse unit in one of the few historically registered residential houses in San Francisco. The building was built in 1865 and is conveniently located in Jackson Square, blocks away from the San Francisco Ferry Building, Embarcadero, Chinatown, North Beach, and the Financial District. Unobstructed views of the Transamerica Building with private rooftop deck and access to an even larger garden patio with a gas grill and gas heaters.

The space
The private unit is a Junior One-Bedroom with a sitting area and full sized desk. A private bathroom, kitchen and dining area are located in a separate room with a private rooftop deck located just off of the kitchen. The rooftop deck has an additional dining area with a dining table and 4 chairs and a separate deck with a lounge chair and side table. There are two gas heaters located on the roof and string lights above. All of the large windows have black out shades to provide privacy.
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is pretty quite and clean as neighboring restaurants spray down their side walks daily. Jackson Square is home to most of the Venture Capital firms located in the city as well as other professional offices and small companies. We are located close to a lively area as North Beach and Chinatown are 1-2 blocks away filled with restaurants, bars and night clubs. Please note that there is a club on the corner of Montgomery and Broadway, half a block from the unit but it is generally quite and offers nightly security to ensure safety on the street. On the other side of the street there is an elementary school which you can hear the children playing outside during school days. We highly encourage everyone to view online maps to get a good sense of the neighborhood as well as our neighbors if this is a concern.
host_about: Hi! WeÃ¢â¬â¢re the HirschfeldÃ¢â¬â¢s and have been in SF for over 15 yrs. I enjoy spending my free time in yoga classes and traveling and trying new things. Our weekends are consumed with enjoying the city and trips up to Sonoma where we have access to small farm.

name: Spacious & Charming 2BR/1BA Unit
description:
Spacious and charming 2BR/1BA Suite with work desks in desirable Lakeshore neighborhood, right across to beautiful Lake Merced Park and TPC Harding Park Golf Course. Conveniently located near Stonestown Galleria featuring Whole Foods, Trader Joe's, Target and many popular restaurants and shopping stores, SF Zoo, Beach, Stern Grove and SFSU. This area is a perfect stay to explore San Francisco!

The space
The 2 bedrooms boast spacious rooms with designer bed frames (firm memory foam mattress), work desks, TV with firestick, electric wall heaters and full size closet.

There is a kitchen and washer/dryer for usage.

Guest access
You will have access to private bedrooms, bathroom and kitchentte.

Other things to note
Even though the ground level room is private and separate, I also live upstairs with two dogs. You may hear muffled voices and footsteps during your stay.

Street cleaning is on 2nd and 4th

name: Powell Place One Bedroom on Nob Hill
description:
Situated in the prestigious Nob Hill section of the city, Powell Place is a charming four-story Edwardian building near the Union Square district. The charm of Powell Place may entice you to spend your entire vacation inside your beautiful vacation home, but venture outside and you'll find access to all of San Francisco by boarding one of the city's cable cars, less than a half-block away.

The space
Our beautiful Carnelian suites feature one bedroom with a queen bed, separate living room with sofa bed, kitchenette, dining area and one bathroom with either a stall shower OR shower/tub combo. Max 4 guests including children.

Please note that the photos are a representation of the unit, and the unit received may look slightly different. Special requests for specific unit numbers cannot be guaranteed. Most units are accessible by stairs only; if you have requests for specific accessibility needs, please note them at checkout when you book your room and con
neighborhood_overview: Powell Place is surrounded by everything that makes San Francisco special. Explore the ethnic culture of Chinatown or visit the Performing Arts Center, where you'll find the Herbst Theater, the War Memorial Opera House, and the Davies Symphony. The San Francisco Museum of Modern Art specializes in contemporary works. For seafood, Fisherman's Wharf is the place to go, and it's right over the hill.

name: Chic, Comfortable, Spacious Studio-Patio & Parking
description:
The apartment is just steps away from Cayuga Park known for its unique themed gardens, whimsical woodcarvings, trails, bustling basketball and tennis courts.

The neighborhood is local, diverse, quiet, and consists of mostly single family homes. Close to freeway access and just 1/2 mile to BART as well as major muni lines.

The spacious living room is chic. The kitchen is well-stocked and has all the amenities to make your stay comfortable. Large open air patio for you morning cup of coffee.
neighborhood_overview:
Located in the Outer Mission area in San Francisco. It is ethnically diverse and is bustling with families. Staying in a local neighborhood is less expensive and yet youÃ¢â¬â¢re just minutes away from the trendy areas of San Francisco. The place is just ÃÂ½ mile to freeway access to South San Francisco, Daly City and the peninsular and the East Bay.

There are colorful murals around the neighborhoods. Casual Mexican and Asian food spots dot the streets, along with diners, corner stores, and ethnic markets.

Outer Mission borders Excelsior District which is home to the Excelsior Festival, an annual event celebrating its cultural diversity. It brings in about 5,000 people each year and has free music and entertainment. There is also Jerry Day, a celebration of the areaÃ¢â¬â¢s most famous former resident, Jerry Garcia, lead singer of the Grateful Dead.
host_about:
I am a graphic designer and a long-time resident of San Francisco.   I am passionate about art, family, the great outdoors and good food.  I volunteer at dog rescue organizations.  

 I have traveled a great deal and understand the frustrations visitors can experience.  San Francisco is a city of only 49 square miles/127 square kilometers, it is unique and very culturally diverse.  As a host, I can help enrich your travel experience in San Francisco and the Bay Area.

The MISSION is the fastest changing neighborhood in SF and has become the bedroom community to the TECH industry and now a group of extremely pampered and well paid 20 something "foodies" that have descended and are slowly taking over. name: Powell Place One Bedroom on Nob Hill
description:
The whole group will enjoy easy access to everything from this centrally located place. Situated in the prestigious Nob Hill section of the city, Powell Place is a charming four-story Edwardian building near the Union Square district. The charm of Powell Place may entice you to spend your entire vacation inside your beautiful vacation home, but venture outside and you'll find access to all of San Francisco by boarding one of the city's cable cars, less than a half-block away.

The space
Our beautiful Carnelian suites feature one bedroom with a queen bed, separate living room with sofa bed, kitchenette, dining area and one bathroom with either a stall shower OR shower/tub combo. Max 4 guests including children.

Please note that the photos are a representation of the unit, and the unit received may look slightly different. Special requests for specific unit numbers cannot be guaranteed. Most units are accessible by stairs only; if you have requests for sp
neighborhood_overview: Powell Place is surrounded by everything that makes San Francisco special. Explore the ethnic culture of Chinatown or visit the Performing Arts Center, where you'll find the Herbst Theater, the War Memorial Opera House, and the Davies Symphony. The San Francisco Museum of Modern Art specializes in contemporary works. For seafood, Fisherman's Wharf is the place to go, and it's right over the hill.

name: Blue House in the Sunnyside
description:
Unwind in this spacious, private unit during your stay. Open concept kitchen/dining/living. Custom woodwork+ hardwood flooring, done by owner, a retired woodworker. Family-friendly neighborhood with great walkability to nearby playgrounds and parks, Glen Park BART and village shops. Street parking and easy freeway access. Washer/dryer in unit. Art cart with supplies for children and adults in kitchen.

The space
A lovely garden entrance greets you as you make your way to the unit's front door. Three rear-facing bedrooms. One with a queen bed, the other two with trundle beds. One bathroom with walk-in shower. A screened off space for this unit's washer/dyer is in the garage, off the kitchen door. While the unit was update and remodeled, it's in an older building, where noise carries. For your convenience, a white noise machine is in the closet of each bedroom, for those sensitive to sound. Street parking only. Backyard is not included in this rental.

<
neighborhood_overview: Sunnyside is a hidden gem. A relatively quiet neighborhood where neighbors greet each other, kids play outside and dogs take their owners out for daily walks:) It feels far removed from the hustle and bustle of the city, yet has fabulous accessibility (25 minutes door to downtown) via Glen Park BART, Muni bus routes and freeway entrances make getting places convenient from here.

You will also be within walking distance of unique landmark sites (Palace of Fine Arts, Lombard Street), outdoor spaces (Crissy Field along the Bay, The Presidio), and three streets with shopping, restaurants, and bars (Union Street, Chestnut Street, Fillmore Street). Within a four-block radius of our listing is the Moscone Park, a laundromat, Safeway, and the Marina Branch Library.
A Laundromat is one block away.
Feel free to contact us for recommendations (we like Shake Shack)!

name: Powell Place Studio on Nob Hill
description:
Situated in the prestigious Nob Hill section of the city, Powell Place is a charming four-story Edwardian building near the Union Square district. The charm of Powell Place may entice you to spend your entire vacation inside your beautiful vacation home, but venture outside and you'll find access to all of San Francisco by boarding one of the city's cable cars, less than a half-block away.

The space
Our beautiful Californian suites feature one bedroom with a queen bed, kitchenette, with either a stall shower OR shower/tub combo. Max 2 guests including children.

Please note that the photos are a representation of the unit, and the unit received may look slightly different. Special requests for specific unit numbers cannot be guaranteed. Most units are accessible by stairs only; if you have requests for specific accessibility needs, please note them at checkout when you book your room and contact the property directly. Units do NOT have A/C.

neighborhood_overview: Powell Place is surrounded by everything that makes San Francisco special. Explore the ethnic culture of Chinatown or visit the Performing Arts Center, where you'll find the Herbst Theater, the War Memorial Opera House, and the Davies Symphony. The San Francisco Museum of Modern Art specializes in contemporary works. For seafood, Fisherman's Wharf is the place to go, and it's right over the hill.
